		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've never done &quot;real&quot; 65816 code, but wouldn't letting A, X and Y 16-bit in most situations be the more sane choice ? It's supposed to be a 16-bit processor after all. You can temporary turn A to 8-bit when dealing with memory mapped I/O, and then revert to 16-bit.

		

